title: Area Football: West Central blanked by Rebels
text: Posted Oct. 10, 2015 at 12:01 AM Posted Oct. 10, 2015 at 12:01 AM BIGGSVILLE â€” The West Central High School football team was held to 82 offensive yards in a 50-0 thumping by LTC foe Stark County on Friday. The Rebels (7-0, 5-0) rolled to a 27-0 lead after the first quarter and tacked on two more TDs in the second quarter for a 40-0 lead at the break. The Heat (0-7, 0-5) picked up just 38 rushing yards and 44 by air in the loss. The Register-Mail
